Package org.joml

Class Matrix4x3dStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joml.Matrix4x3d
      • org.joml.Matrix4x3dStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, Matrix4x3dc
    public class Matrix4x3dStack
extends Matrix4x3d
    A stack of many Matrix4x3d instances. This resembles the matrix stack known from legacy OpenGL.

    This Matrix4x3dStack class inherits from Matrix4x3d, so the current/top matrix is always the Matrix4x3dStack/Matrix4x3d itself. This affects all operations in Matrix4x3d that take another Matrix4x3d as parameter. If a Matrix4x3dStack is used as argument to those methods, the effective argument will always be the current matrix of the matrix stack.

    Author:
    Kai Burjack

      • Matrix4x3dStack

        public Matrix4x3dStack​(int stackSize)
        Create a new Matrix4x3dStack of the given size.

        Initially the stack pointer is at zero and the current matrix is set to identity.

        Parameters:
        stackSize - the size of the stack. This must be at least 1, in which case the Matrix4x3dStack simply only consists of this Matrix4x3d

      • Matrix4x3dStack

        public Matrix4x3dStack()
        Do not invoke manually! Only meant for serialization.

        Invoking this constructor from client code will result in an inconsistent state of the created Matrix4x3dStack instance.
